'''Karim Hafez Ramadan Seifeldin''' ({{langx|ar|كَرِيم حَافِظ رَمَضَان سَيْف الدِّين}}; born 12 March 1996) is an Egyptian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Egyptian Premier League]] club [[Pyramids FC|Pyramids]] and the [[Egypt national football team|Egypt national team]] as a [[Full-back (association football)|left-back]].

==Club career==
Hafez made his top flight debut with Belgian club [[Lierse S.K. (1906)|Lierse S.K.]] on 30 August 2014 against [[Waasland-Beveren]] in a 2–0 away defeat.<ref name="soccerway2">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/08/30/belgium/pro-league/kv-red-star-waasland/koninklijke-lierse-sportkring/1696965/|title=Waasland-Beveren vs. Lierse|date=30 August 2014|publisher=soccerway.com|access-date=18 December 2014}}</ref> On 20 September 2014, he scored his first league goal against [[K.V.C. Westerlo]] in a 6–1 away defeat.<ref name="soccerway3">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/12/07/belgium/pro-league/koninklijke-lierse-sportkring/koninklijke-atletiek-associatie-gent/1477733/?ICID=PL_MS_07|title=Westerlo vs. Lierse – 20 September 2014 – Soccerway|publisher=soccerway.com|access-date=18 December 2014}}</ref> Hafez continued to play for Lierse's senior side and was one of their star performers, scoring three goals in the [[Jupiler Pro League]] but could not save his club from relegation.<ref name="Ghanem">{{Cite web|last=Ghanem|first=Mohaned|date=2015-08-05|title=AEK, Lierse agreement for Karim Hafez's transfer collapses|url=https://www.kingfut.com/2015/08/05/agreement-for-karim-hafezs-transfer-collapses/|access-date=2021-08-07|website=KingFut|language=en-GB}}</ref> Because of his excellent individual play, he was called up to the Egyptian national team by their Argentine manager [[Héctor Cúper]] and made his debut for the Pharaohs in June, coming off the bench in a 2–1 friendly win against [[Malawi national football team|Malawi]].<ref name="Ghanem"/>
 
Maged Sami, the owner of both [[Wadi Degla]] and Lierse, traveled to Athens to negotiate the transfer of Hafez to [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]], and an agreement was expected to be reached over several days in which the 19-year-old Egypt left-back would join the eleven-time Greek champions on loan for a season, with the option to extend the loan for two additional seasons, according to Lierse announcement on their official website. However, the move took a negative turn because of two disagreements. First, Wadi Degla sought the option of first choice if Hafez should be sold because of an offer by another club. Second, they wanted to be paid about €500,000 if AEK were to qualify for the [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] in the 2016–17 season. The disagreements regarding the transfer were augmented when Lierse announced the transfer on their official website before it was final, which AEK Athens did not take kindly to. The deal collapsed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kingfut.com/2015/08/05/agreement-for-karim-hafezs-transfer-collapses/|title=AEK, Lierse agreement for Karim Hafez's transfer collapses|publisher=www.kingfut.com|access-date=5 August 2015}}</ref>

Hafez then played for the French club [[RC Lens]] on loan from Lierse.

On 29 August 2018, Hafez was loaned by Wadi Degla to the Turkish club [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|İstanbul Başakşehir]] for the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibfk.com.tr/hos-geldin-karim-hafez/|title=Welcome to Karim Hafez|publisher=www.ibfk.com|access-date=30 August 2018|archive-date=30 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180830110414/http://www.ibfk.com.tr/hos-geldin-karim-hafez/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

==International career==
In May 2018 he was named in Egypt's preliminary [[Egypt national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 World Cup]] in [[Russia]], but he wasn't selected for the final squad.<ref>{{cite web|title= World Cup 2018: All the confirmed squads for this summer's finals in Russia|url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/440833652018}}{{dead link|date=September 2025|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>

